Super Admin API Flows    
    Super Admin Login:
        API: /super-admin/login
        Method: POST
        Flow:
            1. Validate input data matches schema
            2. If matches, then check if super admin with this email exists
            3. Validate the password of the super admin
            4. Check if the super admin is active
            5. Generate/Fetch JWT token, if generated the super admin's id and user type is used in JWT
            6. Return success response

    New Org registration:
        API: /organizations
        Method: POST
        Flow:
            1. Validate input data matches schema
            2. If matches, then check if organization with this email already exists
            3. If not, then insert new record for the org
            4. Make another entry in the log table
            5. Return success response

    Get All Oregistration:
        API: /organizations
        Method: GET
        Flow:
            1. Fetch all the Organizations which are not deleted, since we do soft deletes, orgs can be filtered by status as well
            2. Calculate offset based on page and limit set, so when fetched the data starts at the offset till the limit
            3. Orgs are sorted in desc order using createdAT
            4. Return success response along with the details of the orgs and some metadata

    Update the status of an Organization:
        API: /organizations/:id/status
        Method: PATCH
        Flow:
            1. Fetch the query params
            2. Validate the request body
            3. Fetch the details of the org by id
            4. Update the status of the org in DB
            5. Make Audit log entry
            6. Return success reponse
        
    Fetch Non-Affliate Requests:
        API: /non-affiliate-requests
        Method: GET
        FLOW:
            1. Fetch all non-affliate requests from the non_affiliate_requests table based on status which if not provided is in query params is set to pending
            2. The requests are sorted by created at in desc order
            3. Return the data with some metadata

    Review Non-Affliate Request:
        API: /non-affiliate-requests/:id/review
        Method: PATCH
        Flow:
            1. Fetch the query params
            2. Validate the request body
            3. Fetch the details of the non-affiliate request by id
            4. Update the status of the non-affiliate request in DB, only Apporved and Rejected status are allowed
            5. Make Audit log entry
            6. Return success reponse

